Washington Street, north from Morton Street, showing a clearance on the west side of this thoroughfare and opposite same the U. S. Government Building known as the U. S. Appraisers
Stores.
This 10 story structure bears No. o4l Washington Street, occupying the entire block bounded by Barrow, Christopher and Greenwich Streets. View No. 2 is taken mainly to show tnis
building.
December 3, 1931
View 1 and 2
P. L. Sperr
